                    div#about-me-image.pixelated
                    div#about-me-description
                        span#about-me-title.content-title ABOUT ME
                        div#about-me-text
                            p.content-text.intro-text Hi! I’m Charlie Yin, a software developer currently based in Vancouver, British Columbia.
                            p.content-text.detail-text I graduated from the University of British Columbia, receiving a Bachelor of Electrical Engineering in 2017. It’s there where I gained a passion in software development. I’ve had the pleasure of working on different projects throughout the years, some of which include developing embedded firmware for robots, implementing distributed real-time networks, and even making this website. I’ve also been able to become proficient in different programming languages like C/C++, JavaScript, Python, and many more. My current interest lies in firmware development and machine learning/artificial intelligence.
                            p.content-text.detail-text Aside from software, I also have big interests in music and art. On the music side, I listen to a lot of jazz and I also frequently play jazz on the piano. On the art side, I enjoy looking at different types of art and have experience in graphics and UI design.

